This press gaggle took place aboard Air Force One on the way back to the United States from South Africa. Jay Carney and Ben Rhodes, Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications, answered questions about President Obama's attendance at Nelson Mandela's memorial service. They discussed the President's speech, his interactions with other world leaders, and his focus on honoring Mandela's legacy. They also mentioned the handshake between President Obama and Raul Castro, and the President's desire for a different relationship with Cuba. Additionally, they mentioned the presence of other leaders at the event and the President's plans for the future.